<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880622-0161 </DOCNO><HL> Metromedia Chairman Acquires 5.9% Stake In NAC Re Shares </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NREC </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   John W. Kluge, chairman of Metromedia Co., said he has acquired a 5.9% stake in NAC Re Corp.'s common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Mr. Kluge said he holds 419,995 NAC Re common shares, including 199,994 shares purchased in private transactions on June 14 for $25 a share.    Mr. Kluge said he acquired the NAC Re stock for investment purposes.    According to the filing, Mr. Kluge is a director of NAC Re, a Greenwich, Conn.-based property and casualty reinsurance concern. Mr. Kluge lives in Charlottesville, Va.    Martha Bannerman, NAC Re's general counsel, said, &quot;We're delighted.&quot; She described Mr. Kluge as &quot;a valued director and shareholder.&quot; Mr. Kluge has been on the NAC Re board since August 1985. </TEXT></DOC>